	<ul class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-paulfirth bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-1222">
		<div id="comment-1222">
		<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e19935619bbfb2c4d003acdb0669ca46?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.wildbunny.co.uk' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Paul Firth</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/2011/12/11/how-to-make-a-2d-platform-game-part-1/comment-page-1/#comment-1222">
			March 2, 2012 at 1:52 pm</a>		</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

		<div class="comment-body"><p>Ok, couple of new functions and some replacements:</p>
<p>Gui/Hud.as</p>
<p><code>///<br />
		///<br />
		///<br />
		public function Hud( defaultLives:int, stage:Stage )<br />
		{<br />
			m_stage = stage;<br />
			m_lifeIcons = new ReferenceArray( HudLifeFla );</p>
<p>			for ( var i:int = 0; i&lt;defaultLives; i++ )<br />
			{<br />
				AddLife( i );<br />
			}<br />
		}</p>
<p>///<br />
		///<br />
		///<br />
		private function AddLife( i:int ):void<br />
		{<br />
			var icon:HudLifeFla = new HudLifeFla( );</p>
<p>			icon.x = i*( icon.width+5 )+Constants.kScreenDimensions.m_x/2;<br />
			icon.y = 5;</p>
<p>			m_lifeIcons.Add( icon );</p>
<p>			m_stage.addChild( icon );<br />
		}</p>
<p>		///<br />
		///<br />
		///<br />
		public function ExtraLife( ):void<br />
		{<br />
			AddLife( m_lifeIcons.m_Num );<br />
		}<br />
</code></p>
<p>Code/Characters/Player.as</p>
<p><code>///<br />
		///<br />
		///<br />
		public function ExtraLife( ):void<br />
		{<br />
			m_lives++;<br />
			m_platformer.ExtraLife( );<br />
		}</code></p>
<p>Code/Platformer.as</p>
<p><code>///<br />
		///<br />
		///<br />
		public function ExtraLife( ):void<br />
		{<br />
			m_hud.ExtraLife( );<br />
		}</code></p>
<p>Then, whenever the player should get an extra life call: m_player.ExtraLife()</p>
<p>Hope that helps!</p>
</div>

