			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e19935619bbfb2c4d003acdb0669ca46?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.wildbunny.co.uk' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Paul Firth</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.wildbunny.co.uk/blog/2011/12/11/how-to-make-a-2d-platform-game-part-1/comment-page-1/#comment-1278">
			March 21, 2012 at 1:47 pm</a>		</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

		<div class="comment-body"><p>Hi Karen,</p>
<p>1) Have you re-built the game in FlashDevelop / Amethyst? FD needs assets.swc exporting to the root of the project.<br />
2) Add this function to Code/Platformer.as</p>
<pre>/// &lt;summary&gt;
/// Remove all moveable objects
/// &lt;/summary&gt;
public function RemoveAllMos():void
{
	for ( var i:int = 0; i<m_moveableobjects .m_Num; i++ )
	{
		var mo:MoveableObject = m_moveableObjects.Get( i );
		
		if ( RemoveMo( mo, false ) )
		{
			i--;
		}
	}
}</pre>
<p>And you can call it from Code.Characters.Player.Died() if you want them to disappear before the start of the next level, or from Code.Platformer.DiedCompletely() if you want them to disappear at the start of next level.</p>
<p>Cheers, Paul.</m_moveableobjects></p>
</div>

